1
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:14,166
[footsteps]

2
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:27,541
[SUZUHA]
So this is where you've been.

3
00:00:27,625 --> 00:00:29,208
I should have guessed.

4
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:31,208
[MAYURI]
Oh, Suzu.

5
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:33,458
Dad and the others
are looking for you.

6
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:36,750
They said they're about
to kick off the operation.

7
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:37,916
Mayu?

8
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,125
[MAYURI]
What if...

9
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,750
What if I'd acted differently?

10
00:00:47,875 --> 00:00:50,791
[MAYURI] If I'd just done
things another way...

11
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:53,041
...and reached my hand out?

12
00:00:53,125 --> 00:00:55,166
Would this future be different?

13
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:09,000
[MAYURI]
That day...

14
00:01:09,083 --> 00:01:12,666
...if my Hikoboshi had
burned bright just once more,

15
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:15,000
it might have changed
everything for us.

16
00:01:17,625 --> 00:01:19,708
[MAYURI]
What if when he fell...

17
00:01:19,791 --> 00:01:21,708
...I'd reached out
and touched him?

18
00:01:50,083 --> 00:01:51,708
[MAN 01A]
You are drifting down.

19
00:01:51,791 --> 00:01:53,833
Plunging through your memories.

20
00:01:53,916 --> 00:01:57,208
As you sink ever deeper,
you see a light.

21
00:01:57,291 --> 00:01:59,625
It entrances you.

22
00:01:59,708 --> 00:02:01,833
Tell me, what color
is the light?

23
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:03,291
It's red.

24
00:02:03,375 --> 00:02:05,208
[MAN 01A] Standing within
this brilliant aura

25
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:08,250
is someone of great
importance to you.

26
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:10,833
Is it a family member?

27
00:02:10,916 --> 00:02:12,541
She's not.

28
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:15,750
Then a friend, perhaps.
Or maybe a lover?

29
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:17,583
[OKABE]
She doesn't even know me.

30
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:19,916
She and I... We haven't...

31
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:29,625
[MAYURI gasps]

32
00:02:29,708 --> 00:02:31,458
[MAYURI]
Okarin!

33
00:02:31,541 --> 00:02:32,416
Uh--

34
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,666
[MAYURI giggles]

35
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:36,125
[OKABE]
Hey, what gives?

36
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:38,541
I told you there was no reason
to wait around for me.

37
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:40,416
[MAYURI chuckles]

38
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,375
How was your session?

39
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:43,708
Good.

40
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:45,291
Turns out hypnotherapy
works well

41
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:47,458
for someone with a
robust temporal lobe.

42
00:02:47,541 --> 00:02:48,916
The doc says I'll be fine.

43
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,625
Wow! You mean it?

44
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:53,041
Yeah, but he does want me
to keep up the counseling

45
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:53,958
for a while.

46
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:55,833
You were right about it helping.

47
00:02:55,916 --> 00:02:57,416
I'm glad I took your advice.

48
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,000
[MAYURI]
That's such a relief.

49
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,250
Honestly, it seemed
like you were

50
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,666
having a pretty
rough time lately.

51
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:04,333
I'm sorry if I worried you.

52
00:03:04,416 --> 00:03:05,416
[MAYURI]
Mm-mm.

53
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,416
How 'bout we go
grab a bite to eat?

54
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,666
It's my treat.

55
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:12,958
In that case, why don't
we head over to Akiba

56
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:14,416
for old time's sake?

57
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,916
[OKABE]
Huh?

58
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,500
[MAYURI] Ruka and Faris invited
me out a little while ago

59
00:03:17,583 --> 00:03:19,333
and it sounded like fun.

60
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:21,000
Akihabara, huh?

61
00:03:22,041 --> 00:03:23,041
Can we?

62
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,625
[OKABE]
Sure. Of course.

63
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:31,708
[MAYURI]
That's the best news!

64
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:34,500
I'll tell everyone we're
on our way. One sec!

65
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:37,375
Hey, Faris!
Guess what! Guess what!

66
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:39,208
[OKABE]
It's cold.

67
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:41,333
Somehow, December already.

68
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:43,833
[OKABE]
And yet...

69
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:46,541
...it feels like the summer
happened moments ago.

70
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:59,250
[door chimes]

71
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,791
Let's see.

72
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:02,750
They said they'd be waiting
in here for us somewhere, so...

73
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,250
[MAYURI gasps]

74
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:06,083
[MAYURI]
Ruka! Faris! We're here!

75
00:04:06,166 --> 00:04:07,083
Too-too-roo!

76
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:08,791
I'm glad you could
make it, Mayuri.

77
00:04:08,875 --> 00:04:10,500
Kyouma!

78
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:13,000
[OKABE]
Rukako. Faris.

79
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:14,750
Been a while since
I've seen you.

80
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,041
We're well aware.

81
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:19,166
[FARIS] Kyouma! I missed
you so much, meow!

82
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,291
[OKABE] Hey! Will you
cut this nonsense out?

83
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:22,541
[FARIS]
What for, meow?

84
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:24,666
Kyouma knows he likes it, meow.

85
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:26,125
[OKABE]
All right. More importantly,

86
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,916
will you please stop
calling me that?

87
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,791
Meow come?

88
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,375
Because it's from the dark past.

89
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:32,958
[FARIS grunts] Just tell me who
I have to paw to get it back!

90
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:35,208
These claws'll show 'em
not to mess with my Kyouma.

91
00:04:35,291 --> 00:04:36,458
--Of course.
--[RUKA] You know,

92
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:38,458
this kinda feels
like the old days.

93
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:40,000
I go to the lab
every now and then,

94
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:43,125
but I never see you
there anymore, Okabe.

95
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:44,583
[OKABE]
Well, I've been quite busy.

96
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:45,750
Don't tell me!

97
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:47,708
You've been captured
by a secret society?

98
00:04:47,791 --> 00:04:51,250
Unfortunately, I'm just swamped
with college seminars.

99
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,625
But there are clubs as well.

100
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:53,625
Meow! Meow!

101
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:55,541
You actually joined a club?

102
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:58,416
Do you guys research UFOs
and Bigfoots and stuff?

103
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,625
No. I'm now a tennis star!

104
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:03,208
--[RUKA] Are you serious?
--[FARIS] What?!

105
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:04,250
[MAYURI chuckles]

106
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:06,166
One of my professors
is the advisor.

107
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:07,833
You'd be shocked
at my proficiency.

108
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:09,875
I never really pegged
you as a sportsman.

109
00:05:09,958 --> 00:05:12,375
[MAYURI] Look out, Wimbledon!
Here comes Okarin.

110
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:13,833
[RUKA]
So practicing day and night

111
00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:15,291
must be why you're
so busy, right?

112
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:18,708
Well, uh, it's not
really that intensive.

113
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,541
Then what have you
been doing without us?

114
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:23,333
[OKABE] Well, if you must know,
I've had some, uh, group dates.

115
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:25,125
--[FARIS] Group?
--[RUKA] Dates!

116
00:05:25,208 --> 00:05:27,000
--[FARIS screams]
--[RUKA] What?!

117
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:28,458
